name: Air North 737-505(WL) [C-GANH] Evening Landing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Air North is one of YYC's lesser-known regular airlines, operating just 5 times a week from Whitehorse and on to Edmonton in the late evening. As you've seen on my channel in the past, they have a sole 737-200 that they rarely fly into YYC, but other times, they'll send one of their 4 737-500s or their sole 737-400. A 737-500 is still a fairly uncommon sight these days, so I believe it's worth sharing. ATC is included, enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
